goals.rationale: This visualization will help us compare the effectiveness of different antibiotics against the bacteria and identify any significant differences.

goals.question: What is the distribution of Streptomycin effectiveness against Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a significant difference in the effectiveness of Streptomycin against Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.

goals.question: Which bacteria are most resistant to Neomycin?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the bacteria that are most resistant to Neomycin and may require alternative treatments.

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of Gram staining results for each genus of bacteria and identify any patterns or trends.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Penicillin'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Penicillin Effectiveness')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin effectiveness against the bacteria?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data[['Penicillin', 'Streptomycin', 'Neomycin']]
    plt.boxplot(data, labels=data.columns)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('How does the effectiveness of Streptomycin compare to that of Penicillin and Neomycin?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

```
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Gram_Staining'] = data['Gram_Staining'].astype('category')
    data['Streptomycin'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Streptomycin'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Streptomycin'])
    data = data[data['Gram_Staining'].isin(['positive', 'negative'])]
    chart_data = [data[data['Gram_Staining'] == 'positive']['Streptomycin'], data[data['Gram_Staining'] == 'negative']['Streptomycin']]
    plt.boxplot(chart_data, labels=['Gram-positive', 'Gram-negative'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Streptomycin effectiveness against Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.sort_values(by='Neomycin', ascending=False)
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', x='Bacteria', y='Neomycin', legend=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Bacteria')
    ax.set_ylabel('Neomycin Effectiveness')
    ax.set_title('Which bacteria are most resistant to Neomycin?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.groupby(['Genus', 'Gram_Staining']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    pivoted = data.pivot(index='Genus', columns='Gram_Staining', values='count')
    pivoted.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, rot=0)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Gram staining results for each genus of bacteria?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
